<TEXT> vigatarāga uvāca|*</TEXT>
        <TR>Vigatarāga spoke:</TR>

% ma-vipulā
<TEXT> manaḥ svavedyaṃ lokānām{ }unmanas{ }tu na vidyate|</TEXT>
        <APP>\va <LEM>manaḥ</LEM> \msCa\msNa\Ed; mana \msCb</APP>
        <TR>The mind is self-evident for people, 
                but the non-mind (Łunmanas$) is not known.</TR>

%folioinfo \msCb\ 465.jpg, f.232r
<TEXT> unmanaḥ kathayāsmākaṃ kīdṛśaṃ lakṣaṇaṃ bhavet||</TEXT> 20:83
        <TR>Teach us about the non-mind, what is its defining mark?</TR>

<TEXT> anarthayajña uvāca|*</TEXT>
        <TR>Anarthayajña spoke:</TR>

<TEXT> unmanastvaṃ gate vipra nibodha daśalakṣaṇam|</TEXT>
        <APP>\vb <LEM>nibodha</LEM> \msCb\msNa\Ed; \lac1 × bodha \msCa</APP>
        <TR>Hear the ten chacteristic marks of someone who 
                has entered the state of the non-mind, O Brahmin.</TR>

<TEXT> na śabdaṃ śṛṇute śrotraṃ śaṅkhabherīsvanād{ }api||</TEXT> 20:84
        <APP>\vc <LEM>śabdaṃ</LEM> \msCa\msNa\Ed; śabda \msCb\oo
                 <LEM>śrotraṃ</LEM> \msCa\msCb\msNa; śrotre \Ed</APP>
        <TR>His ears do not hear any sound, not even the sound
                 of conch-shells and kettle-drums.</TR>
%folioinfo \Ed\ p.661

<TEXT> tvacaḥ sparśaṃ na jānāti śītoṣṇam{ }api duḥsaham|</TEXT>
        <TR>His skin does not know touch,
                 not even unbearable cold or hotness.</TR>

<TEXT> rūpaṃ paśyati no cakṣuḥ parvatābhyadhiko 'pi vā||</TEXT> 20:85
        <TR>His eyes do not see any forms, not even things
                         bigger than mountains.</TR>

<TEXT> jihvā rasaṃ na vindeta madhurāmlavaṇo 'pi vā|</TEXT>
        <APP>\vb <LEM>°rāmlavaṇo</LEM> \corr; °rāmlavano \msCa\msNa, 
                                    °ro lavano \msCb, °rāmlavato \Ed</APP>
        <TR>His tongue does not sense tastes,
                         not even sweetness or saltiness.</TR>

<TEXT> gandhaṃ jighrati na ghrāṇā tīkṣṇaṃ vāpy{ }aśucīny{ }api||</TEXT> 20:86
        <APP>\vc <LEM>ghrāṇā</LEM> \mssALL\msCa\msCb\msNa; ghrāṇo \Ed</APP>
        <APP>\vd <LEM>vāpy{ }aśucī°</LEM> \mssALL\msCa\msNa\Ed; vāpi śucī° \msCb</APP>
        <TR>His nose does not sense smells,
                 not even strong or impure ones.</TR>

<TEXT> unmanas{ }tv{ }eṣa me khyātaṃ sarvadvaitavināśanam|</TEXT>
        <APP>\va <LEM>unmanas{ }tv{ }eṣa me</LEM> \msCb\msNa;
                                \lac6 ×××××× \msCa, 
                                unmanas{ }tava me \Ed</APP>
